The paper deals with the problem of exploring temporal graphs, which is a topic in graph theory and algorithms. The paper presents results on the complexity of the problem and provides algorithms for exploring temporal graphs under different assumptions about the underlying graph. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also deals with graph theory, which suggests categories such as cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also presents distributed algorithms, which suggests categories such as cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
